From: Petr Mladek <pmladek@suse.com>
Date: Fri, 10 Apr 2026 15:59:03 -2000
Subject: kABI: Include pool_id bits from work_bits into kABI tracking
Patch-mainline: Never, kABI specific
References: bsc#1260522

The position of pool_id bits is _not_ present in the symtypes data
stored in the kabi/ directory. Therefore, the regular kABI stability
check cannot report any breakage.

However, WORK_OFFQ_POOL_SHIFT, and WORK_OFFQ_POOL_BITS are used
to define WORK_STRUCT_NO_POOL which is later used in WORK_DATA_INIT
and WORK_DATA_STATIC_INIT. Namely, the pool_id bits are initialized
to the max value which is interpreted at that no pool is associated.

Include the position and the number of pool_id bits in kABI tracking
by defining an explicit variable that depends on them.

Suggested-by: Michal Koutný <mkoutny@suse.com>
Signed-off-by: Petr Mladek <pmladek@suse.com>
---
 kernel/workqueue.c |    8 ++++++++
 1 file changed, 8 insertions(+)

--- a/kernel/workqueue.c
+++ b/kernel/workqueue.c
@@ -55,6 +55,14 @@
 
 #include "workqueue_internal.h"
 
+/* SL-specific kABI tracking */
+#define EXPORT_ENUM_VALUE(name) \
+	char (*const __kabi_enum_##name)[name]; \
+	EXPORT_SYMBOL_GPL(__kabi_enum_##name)
+
+EXPORT_ENUM_VALUE(WORK_OFFQ_POOL_SHIFT);
+EXPORT_ENUM_VALUE(WORK_OFFQ_POOL_BITS);
+
 enum worker_pool_flags {
 	/*
 	 * worker_pool flags
